# Glitch documentation discipline

## Intent

- Document the code and behavior that exist today.
- Keep ownership clear so each package documents its own surface.

## Guardrails

- Do not present `apps/app` as a finished product.
- Do not assume an `apps/docs` app exists.
- Use exact route names, file paths, type names, and environment variable names.
- Keep technical docs separate from marketing copy.

## Ownership

- `apps/api/README.md` owns API behavior and env requirements.
- `apps/website/README.md` owns website-specific setup and behavior.
- `ninjatrader/Glitch/Docs` owns AddOn and Indicator product docs.

## Trigger for updates

- When behavior, contracts, or env requirements change, update the owning docs in the same pass.
